The Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol ('''PPTP''') is [[Article description::a method for creating virtual private networks.]] PPTP allows the [[Wikipedia:Point-to-Point_Protocol|Point-to-Point Protocol]] (PPP) to be tunneled through an IP network on TCP port 1723. PPTP has many security vulnerabilities and is considered obsolete.

